{:itonami.blueprint/id "cloud-itonami-isic-1392"
 :itonami.blueprint/name "Manufacture of made-up textile articles, except apparel"
 :itonami.blueprint/isic-rev5 "1392"
 :itonami.blueprint/domain :made-up-textile-articles/plant-operations
 :itonami.blueprint/license "AGPL-3.0-or-later"
 :itonami.blueprint/social-impact [:worker-safety :equipment-safety :product-quality-assurance]
 :itonami.blueprint/governor :made-up-textile-articles-operations-governor
 :itonami.blueprint/robotics true
 :itonami.blueprint/required-technologies [:robotics :identity :forms :dmn :bpmn :audit-ledger :cae]
 :itonami.blueprint/status :public-oss
 :itonami.blueprint/maturity :implemented
 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "MadeUpTextileAdvisor ⊣ Made-Up Textile Articles Operations Governor,
 langgraph-clj StateGraph, append-only audit ledger. A plant OPERATIONS
 COORDINATION actor for made-up textile articles manufacturing
 (cutting/sewing/hemming/quilting lines producing bedding, curtains,
 towels, and table linens from finished fabric -- ISIC Rev.5 1392,
 distinct from apparel manufacturing [1410] and from carpets/rugs
 [1393]) -- not direct cutting/sewing-line control authority. Four ops
 (`:log-production-batch` / `:schedule-maintenance` /
 `:flag-safety-concern` / `:coordinate-shipment`), all `:effect
 :propose` only. Ten concrete governor checks elaborate this
 blueprint's four HARD invariants: propose-only effect, closed op
 allowlist, closed proposal-effect allowlist (no direct cutting/
 sewing-line-equipment control), permanent direct-operate block,
 independent equipment verification/registration before maintenance
 scheduling, independent batch verification/registration before
 shipment coordination, independent shipment-quantity recompute
 against the batch's own logged finished-unit count, double-schedule
 guard, quality-grade validation, and defect-rate plausibility
 validation. Safety-concern flagging (equipment-safety/quality-defect)
 ALWAYS escalates to a human plant supervisor; `:log-production-batch`
 is the only op eligible to auto-commit, and only at phase 3 when
 governor-clean."}
